Dreamworks currently has a petition to remake the first two film adaptations. As long as they are more true to the books what could be better than that? I was also surprised Rick Riordan liked that the characters were played by older actors. It is his book, so he has all rights and say to it. This got a 6/10 rating from me. I've watched it and I liked it so much that when my wife came home I've played the movie for a second time and while watching it I was translating to her, step by step what was my interpretation of their dialogue in Mayan. Anyways, weeks later, by accident I've found the subtitles hidden by mistake in a submenu and when I've played it I was shocked to discover that my explanations were spot on, almost 100%. The whole movie is perfect; the way it was directed, the scenes, the script, the characters and their flawless act, everything is so beautifully put together that you can watch it with no subtitles at all. Try it. This is a work of a genius.
PS
Later on I've bought a legit dvd for my good movies collection. It deserves this statute
